               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440304-name-867" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-867" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-867" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-867" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN SMITH</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Charles-street, St. Luke's; Drake was in my ser<lb></lb>vice. On Tuesday the 20th of Feb. I missed my watch—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440304-name-868" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-868" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-868" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-868" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS SMITH</persName>
                  </hi>. Drake came in to my father's for his two days' wages—he said, "Where is your father?"—I said, "He is gone out; he won't be long; will you sit down?"—he sat down, and said, "Let me see what time it is?"—he stood up, took the watch down, and looked at it—I said, "If you don't put it back, my father will come in, and you will get into trouble"—he said he wanted to go to the water-closet, and went away with the watch.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440304-name-869" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-869" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-869" type="surname" value="MURRAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-869" type="given" value="BENJAMIN RICHARD"></interp>BENJAMIN RICHARD MURRAY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker. I took in this watch of a man on the 24th of Feb.—I cannot identify him—this is the duplicate I gave him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440304-name-870" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-870" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-870" type="surname" value="BERRIDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-870" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BERRIDGE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable G</hi> 40.) I apprehended Drake'at a public-house in Liquorpond-street on the 28th of Feb.—I asked if he had taken a watch—he said yes, and given it to a man to pledge—he gave me this duplicate of it—he said, he had received half-a-crown out of 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440304-name-871" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-871" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-871" type="surname" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440304-name-871" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES THOMAS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable G</hi> 139.) I took Kirby—I told him he was charged with receiving a watch that had been stolen—he said a boy had given it him to pledge, and he had pledged it for him in Gray's-inn-road, and given the boy half-a-crown out of the money.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Kirby's Defence.</hi> Drake came to me and said, "I was coming down Bar<lb></lb>bican just now, and found a watch in an old black handkerchief;" I said, "you rascal, you have stolen it;" he said, "No, I picked it up;" I said, "Why don't you take it home?" he said he had got no home, and he should be obliged if I would sell or pawn it for him; I went where my wife generally goes, and put it in my own name and address; it was getting late;</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184403040103"></xptr>
               <p>I said to Drake, "What are you going to do with the money?" he said, "I am going to Duke's-place to buy oranges, and get my living;" I said, "I will give you half-a-crown, and when you want more you can have it."</p>
               <p>
